# Backend (MeetIQ) — Human-Owned

The human dev owns this code. The AI agent **must not generate full implementations** here.

## Allowed AI behavior in `backend/`

- Hints, explanations, debugging guidance.
- Pointing out architectural issues with reasoning.
- Sketching small TS interfaces or schema snippets when explicitly asked.
- Reviewing diffs for bugs when asked.

## Disallowed

- Writing full controllers, services, repositories, or routes unprompted.
- Refactoring existing code without permission.
- Adding dependencies without asking.
- Bypassing the layered architecture below.

## Architecture (controller / service / repository)

```
backend/src/
  modules/
    <feature>/
      <feature>.controller.ts   # HTTP layer — parse req, call service, shape res
      <feature>.service.ts      # Business logic — pure-ish, no Express types
      <feature>.repository.ts   # DB access via Prisma — no business logic
      <feature>.routes.ts       # Wire controller methods to Express routes
      <feature>.schema.ts       # Zod input/output schemas
  middleware/
  lib/                          # prisma client, redis, bullmq, openai
  types/
  index.ts                      # bootstrap (express, socket.io)
```

### Layer Rules

- **Controller**: thin. Only req/res, validation via Zod, calls service. No DB calls.
- **Service**: business rules. Pure functions where possible. No Express, no `req`/`res`.
- **Repository**: Prisma-only. One repo per aggregate. No cross-aggregate joins in repo — compose in service.
- **Routes**: declarative. No logic.

## Stack reminders (for guidance only)

- Express + TypeScript
- Prisma + PostgreSQL
- Socket.IO (chat, meeting events) — its own gateway module
- Redis + BullMQ (transcript/summarization jobs)
- OpenAI API (post-meeting AI pipeline)
- JWT auth (refresh + access split recommended)
- AWS S3 / Cloudflare R2 for recordings

## When the human asks for help

1. Ask what they tried first if unclear.
2. Give the smallest hint that unblocks them.
3. Only write code if they say "fix it" or "write it".
